io.sphere.sdk.client

Class SolutionInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.sphere.sdk.models.Base
      • io.sphere.sdk.client.SolutionInfo

  • public class SolutionInfo
extends Base
    Marker interface to generate a solution info for the JVM SDK user agent.

    A User-Agent header with a solution information looks like this: commercetools-sdk-java-v1/1.4.1 (AHC/2.0) Java/1.8.0_92-b14 (Mac OS X; x86_64) SOLUTION_NAME/SOLUTION_VERSION (+https://website.tld; +info@SOLUTION.com)

    To add a solution information to the JVM SDK create a resource file src/main/resources/META-INF/services/io.sphere.sdk.client.SolutionInfo which contains a fully qualified class name like (replace at least SOLUTION with your solution name) tld.SOLUTION.client.SOLUTIONSolutionInfo

    Then create a class tld.SOLUTION.client.SOLUTIONSolutionInfo: 
     
     public class SOLUTIONSolutionInfo extends SolutionInfo {
         public SOLUTIONSolutionInfo() {
             setName("JVM-SDK-integration-tests");
             setVersion(BuildInfo.version());
             setWebsite("https://github.com/commercetools/commercetools-jvm-sdk");
             setEmergencyContact("helpdesk@commercetools.com");
         }
     }
    This class will be loaded via reflection.
